          'Hardly an Indian exists who has not seen the scene: a customer offers a ten-rupee coin, the shopkeeper pulls back his hand — "this one doesn’t run." That single sentence has locked crores of legal coins in drawers over the years. The truth is as plain as the rumour is stubborn: the Reserve Bank of India has clarified repeatedly, in writing, that ten-rupee coins of all designs are fully legal tender — ten radiating lines or fifteen, with the ₹ symbol or without it.',
